# Enterprise ERP — Master Architecture & Contract Rules

This document is the single source of truth for all frontend architecture, API contracts, permissions, error handling, environment configuration, and testing standards.

Designed for: large business systems, modular domains, long-term maintainability, AI-assisted development, high scalability, multi-team collaboration, future microservices, Turborepo compatibility.

The architecture must remain: clean, composable, modular, predictable, scalable, RTL-first, premium-quality.

---

# 1. Core Architecture Philosophy

Always prioritize: separation of concerns, composability, modularity, server-first rendering, reusable systems, predictable structure, maintainable codebases, minimal client-side JavaScript.

Avoid monolithic implementations. Large systems must be split into isolated feature modules.

---

# 2. Project Structure — Route / Feature Parity (Required)

**Rule:** `features/` MUST mirror the URL segments under `app/`. Every routable page in `app/` has a matching feature segment with the same folder path (excluding route groups like `(app)` and files like `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`).

| App route (example) | Feature path (required) |
|----------------------|-------------------------|
| `app/(app)/hr/organization/branches/page.tsx` | `features/hr/organization/branches/` |
| `app/(app)/hr/organization/departments/page.tsx` | `features/hr/organization/departments/` |
| `app/(app)/hr/organization/job-titles/page.tsx` | `features/hr/organization/job-titles/` |
| `app/(app)/hr/organization/employees/page.tsx` | `features/hr/organization/employees/` |
| `app/(app)/hr/organization/chart/page.tsx` | `features/hr/organization/chart/` |
| `app/(app)/hr/contracts/employment/page.tsx` | `features/hr/contracts/employment/` |

src/
│
├── app/                              # Routing ONLY — thin entrypoints
│   └── (app)/hr/
│       ├── organization/
│       │   ├── branches/page.tsx
│       │   ├── departments/page.tsx
│       │   ├── job-titles/page.tsx
│       │   ├── employees/page.tsx
│       │   ├── chart/page.tsx
│       │   └── layout.tsx
│       ├── contracts/
│       ├── attendance/
│       ├── leaves/
│       ├── requests/
│       └── ...
│
├── features/                         # Same tree as app routes (business logic)
│   ├── hr/
│   │   ├── organization/             # Domain parent (module-wide shared code)
│   │   │   ├── constants/            # e.g. nav routes for whole organization module
│   │   │   ├── branches/
│   │   │   │   ├── components/
│   │   │   │   ├── hooks/
│   │   │   │   ├── dialogs/
│   │   │   │   └── constants/
│   │   │   ├── departments/
│   │   │   ├── job-titles/
│   │   │   ├── employees/
│   │   │   └── chart/
│   │   ├── contracts/
│   │   ├── attendance/
│   │   ├── leaves/
│   │   └── requests/
│   └── auth/
│
├── components/                       # Generic UI + cross-domain shared UI
├── shared/                           # App shell ONLY (see §2b): config, utils, export, app-session
└── ...

**No monolithic `src/lib/api/` for domain resources.** **No `src/types/`** — types live only under `features/**/types/`.

**Forbidden:** Flat feature folders that skip route segments (e.g. `features/hr/branches/` when the route is `/hr/organization/branches`). **Forbidden:** Page UI living under `features/hr/organization/components/` when the route is `/hr/organization/chart` — use `features/hr/organization/chart/components/` instead.

**Domain parent folder** (`features/hr/organization/`): Module-wide shared pieces — `constants/`, `lib/`, `types/`, optional layout helpers. Do NOT put a single page’s screen in `components/` here.

