# 2b. `lib/` and `types/` — Co-located in Features (Required)

**Principle:** Infrastructure and types live **next to the code that owns them**, not in a global `src/lib/` or `src/types/` bucket.

### Where `lib/` lives

| Scope | Path | Contains |
|-------|------|----------|
| App shell | `src/shared/config/`, `src/shared/utils.ts`, `src/shared/export/` | `publicConfig`, `cn()`, env — **no domain API** |
| HR domain | `features/hr/lib/api/` | `client.ts`, `types.ts` (envelope), `global-error-handler.ts` |
| Organization module | `features/hr/organization/lib/api/` | `branches.ts`, `departments.ts`, `companies.ts`, `jobTitles.ts`, `organization-context.ts` |
| Auth | `features/auth/lib/api/` | `auth.ts` |
| Other domains | `features/{domain}/lib/` | Domain clients, helpers, stores being migrated |

**Per-page folder** (`features/hr/organization/branches/`): `services/`, `hooks/`, `types/`, `components/` — add `lib/` only for helpers used by that page alone.

**Forbidden:**
- `src/lib/api/branches.ts` (and any domain REST client at repo root)
- `src/lib/attendance/`, `src/lib/hr-discipline/` as permanent homes — migrate to `features/hr/attendance/lib/`, etc.
- Importing organization API from `@/lib/api/*` in new code (legacy `@/lib/api/*` re-exports exist temporarily)

### Where `types/` lives

| Type | Path |
|------|------|
| Employee | `features/hr/organization/employees/types/` |
| Contract enums | `features/hr/contracts/types/` |
| Attendance / Shift | `features/hr/attendance/types/` |
| HR requests | `features/hr/requests/types/` |
| Payslip / payroll | `features/hr/payroll/types/` |
| Permissions / roles | `features/hr/permissions/types.ts` (single file if no subfolder) |
| Legacy org list mocks | `features/hr/organization/types/` |
| HERE Maps ambient `.d.ts` | `components/here-map/here-maps.d.ts` (next to the component) |

**Forbidden:** `src/types/` or any root-level business type barrel. Import from the owning feature `types/` path.

**Import examples:**
```ts
import { apiRequest } from '@/features/hr/lib/api/client';
import { handleApiError } from '@/features/hr/lib/api/global-error-handler';
import { branchesApi } from '@/features/hr/organization/lib/api/branches';
import type { Employee } from '@/features/hr/organization/employees/types';
```

