# 4. Feature Module Rules

Every routable area lives under `features/` with the **same path as `app/`** (see §2).

**Per-page feature folder** (e.g. `features/hr/organization/branches/`):
```
branches/
├── components/          # Page root + list views (branches-page.tsx)
├── hooks/               # useBranchesDirectoryModel, etc.
├── dialogs/
├── constants/
├── types/               # Page-owned types (DTOs, view models)
├── utils/
├── services/            # API orchestration — calls domain `lib/api/*`
├── lib/                 # Optional — page-private helpers only
└── index.ts             # optional public exports
```

**Domain parent** (e.g. `features/hr/organization/`) may also have:
```
organization/
├── lib/api/             # Module-shared API clients
├── types/               # Module-shared types
├── constants/
├── branches/            # Per-route segment (mirrors app/)
└── chart/
```

**Rules:**
- One primary `*-page.tsx` component per route, exported for `app/.../page.tsx`.
- Child routes get their own segment (`employees/[id]` → `employees/components/employee-detail-page.tsx`).
- Features must stay isolated; no imports from sibling pages unless through the **domain parent** `lib/`, `types/`, or `constants/`.
- Cross-domain logic → `components/shared/` or the owning feature’s `lib/`.

**Import convention:** `@/features/{same path as app}/{segment}/components/...`

