# 5. Component Architecture Rules

Components must be small and composable.

Forbidden: giant components, giant JSX trees, multi-responsibility components, inline mega dialogs, deeply nested rendering logic.

Size Limits:
- No component may exceed 300 lines
- Prefer extraction before 200 lines
- JSX blocks over 80–100 lines should become separate components

Extract a component when: JSX becomes large, a section becomes independent, local state grows, logic becomes reusable, dialogs/modals appear, a section can evolve independently.

Feature Composition Pattern:
EmployeeDetailPage
├── EmployeeHeader
├── PersonalSection
├── EmploymentSection
├── AttendanceSection
├── SalarySection
├── PermissionsSection
└── ContractsSection

Sections Structure:
components/
└── sections/
    ├── personal-section.tsx
    ├── employment-section.tsx
    ├── attendance-section.tsx
    ├── salary-section.tsx
    └── permissions-section.tsx

Dialog Rules — every dialog must live in its own file:
dialogs/
├── employee-shift-dialog.tsx
├── employee-checkpoint-dialog.tsx
└── employee-contract-dialog.tsx

components/ui/ → presentation-only (no business logic, no feature coupling)
components/shared/ → business-aware reusable components

