# 6. Authorization & Permissions

Principle: Authorization is backend-driven but enforced in frontend for UX only.

Permission Format:
resource:action
Examples: employee:create, employee:edit, payroll:view, request:approve

Frontend Usage — unified helper:
can("employee:create")

Rules:
- Backend is the source of truth — never rely on frontend permissions for security
- Frontend only controls visibility & UX
- Unauthorized access must always be blocked by backend

UI Behavior:
- Hide buttons if user lacks permission
- Disable actions if partially allowed
- Redirect if user accesses forbidden routes

